{"TopicId":165124,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Using Infernal Robotics for an articulated trailer?","CreatedByName":"Jamilton","CreatedById":181107,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T16:15:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jamilton","CreatedById":181107,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-03T16:15:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst forum post because I\u0027m slightly stuck. I\u0027m attempting to create an articulated trailer using Infernal Robotics. I am rather new to IR, but hoped that by having a free moving docking washer, I could attach something to it and it would rotate freely. Which failed. So I tried putting it on the base of a docking port, which would connect to another docking port on top of which was another washer... Which failed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny help and suggestions would be lovely!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-04T04:48:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCouldn\u0027t you achieve this by using a klaw with the pivot unlocked?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-04T17:44:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223164477\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221504500510\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCouldn\u0027t you achieve this by using a klaw with the pivot unlocked?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr maybe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E. (A klaw sounds good too).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-04T18:35:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can do articulated\u00A0trailers pretty easily in the stock game. Also welcome to the forums!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s some examples from my latest Career save:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022CmTAIdc.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/CmTAIdc.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002203o3SvC.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/03o3SvC.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00226Yi4xZ3.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/6Yi4xZ3.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KCVJgLI.jpg\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/KCVJgLI.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-04T18:36:27Z\u0022 title=\u002209/04/2017 06:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jamilton","CreatedById":181107,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-04T19:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m aware of stock articulation, and I have tried using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E (i.e. a winch and a socket) as an alternative, but the former is um.. Not very secure. And the latter is rather floppy. I may emulate those screenshots but with tweakscale to keep it a little bit more compact. Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}